Demand and MR shift to the left in the long-run, which makes the demand curve tangent to the ATC graph. Although there are still profits, the margin is smaller. Profits may continue, but at a smaller magnitude. There are zero profits at a perfectly competitive industry as profits become zero in the long-run for perfectly competitive industries. MR becomes flat, which shows a normalized price for the product. In monopolistic competition, there are still profits in the long run.

